page "features" {
    div class="page-header" {
        h1 { "Features" }
        p class="page-sub" {
            "v3.1 · v3.0 · Store · Validation · SSG · i18n · WASM · Tree-shaking · CSP · Critical CSS · HMR"
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section doc-section-highlight" {
        h2 {
            "v3.1 — LSP quick-fixes (code actions) "
            span class="version-tag version-tag-new" { "new" }
        }
        p {
            "Press "
            code { "Ctrl+." }
            " (VS Code) or "
            code { "ga" }
            " (Neovim) on any unknown identifier to get a quick-fix. Two actions are available:"
        }
        div class="callout" {
            strong { "Import component 'X'" }
            " — cursor on an uppercase identifier not yet imported → prepends "
            code { "import X from \"./X.webc\"" }
            " at the top of the file."
        }
        div class="callout" {
            strong { "Add 'x' to state" }
            " — cursor on an unknown lowercase variable → inserts "
            code { "x: String = \"\"" }
            " into the nearest "
            code { "state {}" }
            " block."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "v3.1 — Semantic tokens "
            span class="version-tag" { "v3.1" }
        }
        p {
            "The LSP server implements "
            code { "textDocument/semanticTokens/full" }
            ". VS Code and Neovim use the token stream for accurate syntax highlighting — keywords, types, string literals, comments, state variables, computed (read-only), and class/component names each get a distinct colour."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "v3.1 — Real-time LSP diagnostics "
            span class="version-tag" { "v3.1" }
        }
        p {
            "The built-in LSP server now pushes "
            code { "textDocument/publishDiagnostics" }
            " notifications on every "
            code { "didOpen" }
            " and "
            code { "didChange" }
            ". Syntax errors appear as squiggles in your editor instantly — no need to run "
            code { "webc check" }
            " manually."
        }
        p {
            "Error ranges are computed from the "
            code { "Span.start" }
            " / "
            code { "Span.end" }
            " byte offsets stored in the AST, giving sub-character precision. "
            code { "didClose" }
            " clears diagnostics so stale squiggles never linger."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section doc-section-highlight" {
        h2 {
            "v3.0 — Core advances "
            span class="version-tag" { "v3.0" }
        }
        p {
            "Three architectural shifts in v3.0 that reduce output size and eliminate the last CSP exception."
        }

        h3 { "1 — Compiled expressions (no unsafe-eval)" }
        p {
            "In v2, expressions like "
            code { "@if count > 0" }
            " were stored as strings in HTML attributes and evaluated at runtime via "
            code { "new Function()" }
            " — requiring "
            code { "script-src 'unsafe-eval'" }
            " in the CSP."
        }
        p {
            "In v3, every expression is compiled to a JS closure at build time."
            " A "
            code { "const _e" }
            " map is emitted inline and the bind functions call closures directly — "
            code { "evalCond" }
            " does not exist in the runtime."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// v2 — string stored in DOM, eval'd at runtime
<div data-webcore-if=\"count > 0\">
<!-- runtime does: new Function('...return count>0')() -->

// v3 — closure compiled at build time, zero eval
<div data-webcore-if=\"e0\">
<script>
const _e = {
  e0: ()=>S.get('count')>0,
  e1: ()=>S.get('count')*2,
};
bindIf(_e); bind(_e);
</script>"
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            strong { "CSP: " }
            code { "Content-Security-Policy: script-src 'self'" }
            " works without "
            code { "unsafe-eval" }
            " — guaranteed structurally, not by configuration."
        }

        h3 { "2 — Build-time component imports" }
        p {
            "Components declare their dependencies at the top of the file."
            " The compiler resolves, loads and inlines them at build time — no runtime module loader."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// Each page only compiles the components it imports
import Button  from \"./Button.webc\"
import Counter from \"./Counter.webc\"

page \"home\" {
    Counter {}
    Button label=\"Go\" {}
}
// dist/index.html — contains Button + Counter code, nothing else
// dist/about/index.html — contains only Button code (if about.webc imports only Button)"
        }

        h3 { "3 — Prod identifier renaming" }
        p {
            "In "
            code { "prod" }
            " mode, runtime identifiers are renamed in a post-pass: "
            code { "bindIf→_bi" }
            ", "
            code { "bindFor→_bf" }
            ", "
            code { "bindAttrs→_ba" }
            "…"
            " Applied after full code generation — the readable names are preserved in dev mode."
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Dev name" }
                    th { "Prod name" }
                    th { "Dev name" }
                    th { "Prod name" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr {
                        td { code { "bind(" } }         td { code { "_b(" } }
                        td { code { "bindIf" } }         td { code { "_bi" } }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { code { "bindFor" } }        td { code { "_bf" } }
                        td { code { "bindAttrs" } }      td { code { "_ba" } }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { code { "bindClassBindings" } } td { code { "_bc" } }
                        td { code { "bindValidation" } }    td { code { "_bv" } }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { code { "bindDefer" } }      td { code { "_bd" } }
                        td { code { "rebindComputed" } }  td { code { "_rc" } }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout" {
            "Activate with "
            code { "prod = true" }
            " in "
            code { "webc.toml" }
            " (or "
            code { "HtmlPageOptions { prod: true }" }
            " programmatically). Estimated gain: 25–30 % on the inline script size."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 { "Global store" }
        p {
            "The "
            code { "store { }" }
            " block declares reactive state shared across all components and pages."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// app.webc
store {
    count:  Number  = 0
    theme:  String  = \"dark\"
    active: Boolean = false
}

// Any component — prefix with $store.
component Display {
    view {
        p \"Global count: \{$store.count}\"
        button on:click=\{$store.count += 1} { \"+\" }
    }
}

component Badge {
    view {
        @if $store.active {
            span \"Active\"
        } @else {
            span \"Inactive\"
        }
    }
}"
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            strong { "Scoped reactivity: " }
            "Store vars use the same "
            code { "S.set() / S.get()" }
            " machinery as component state. Any binding that reads "
            code { "$store.x" }
            " automatically re-renders when "
            code { "$store.x" }
            " changes — no subscription boilerplate."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 { "Form validation" }
        p { "Declarative validation attributes on inputs — no JS event wiring needed." }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component SignupForm {
    view {
        form on:submit=\{handleSubmit} {
            label \"Username\"
            input type=\"text\" name=\"username\"
                  validate:required=\"Username is required\"
                  validate:minlength=\"3,At least 3 characters\"
            @error \"username\" {
                span class=\"error-msg\" \"Check your username\"
            }
            label \"Email\"
            input type=\"email\" name=\"email\"
                  validate:required=\"Email is required\"
                  validate:email=\"Must be a valid email\"
            @error \"email\" {
                span class=\"error-msg\" \"Check your email\"
            }
            button type=\"submit\" { \"Sign up\" }
        }
    }
}"
        }
        p {
            "Validation fires on "
            code { "blur" }
            " and "
            code { "submit" }
            ". "
            code { "@error" }
            " blocks are hidden by default; shown when the corresponding field fails."
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Attribute" }
                    th { "Format" }
                    th { "Description" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr { td { code { "validate:required" } } td { "\"message\"" } td { "Field must not be empty" } }
                    tr { td { code { "validate:minlength" } } td { "\"n,message\"" } td { "Minimum character count" } }
                    tr { td { code { "validate:maxlength" } } td { "\"n,message\"" } td { "Maximum character count" } }
                    tr { td { code { "validate:email" } } td { "\"message\"" } td { "Email format check" } }
                    tr { td { code { "validate:pattern" } } td { "\"regex,message\"" } td { "Custom regex" } }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout" {
            "Validation logic uses the browser's native "
            code { "input.checkValidity()" }
            " capture phase, so no custom regex engine is shipped. The "
            code { "validateField()" }
            " helper is tree-shaken out if no "
            code { "validate:*" }
            " attributes appear in the document."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 { "Static Site Generation (SSG)" }
        p {
            "The compiler pre-renders initial state into HTML at build time. "
            "No flash of unstyled or wrong content on first paint."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// .webc source — state: count = 0
p \"Counter: \{count}\"
@if count > 0 { p \"Positive\" } @else { p \"Zero\" }

// HTML output (SSG pre-rendered)
<p>Counter: <span data-webcore-interpolation=\"count\">0</span></p>
<div data-webcore-if=\"count > 0\" style=\"display:none\">...</div>
<div data-webcore-else=\"count > 0\" style=\"display:block\">...</div>"
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            strong { "Zero JS on first paint: " }
            "The server sends fully populated HTML. The runtime attaches to existing DOM nodes via "
            code { "data-webcore-*" }
            " attributes rather than replacing them, so the initial render is instant and crawlable."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 { "Internationalisation (i18n)" }
        p {
            "Place "
            code { ".toml" }
            " files in "
            code { "locales/" }
            ". Use "
            code { "t(\"key\")" }
            " in views. Switch locale at runtime with "
            code { "setLocale(code)" }
            "."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// locales/en.toml
welcome   = \"Welcome\"
increment = \"Increment\"

// locales/fr.toml
welcome   = \"Bienvenue\"
increment = \"Incrementer\"

// Component view
h1 \"\{t(\"welcome\")}\"
button on:click=\{count += 1} { \"\{t(\"increment\")}\" }
button on:click=\{setLocale(\"fr\")} { \"FR\" }
button on:click=\{setLocale(\"en\")} { \"EN\" }"
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "i18n: parameters and pluralization "
            span class="version-tag" { "v1.1.0" }
        }
        p {
            "Pass a second argument to "
            code { "t()" }
            " for pluralization or positional substitution."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// locales/en.toml
items_one   = \"\{\{count}} item\"
items_other = \"\{\{count}} items\"
greeting    = \"Hello, \{\{0}}!\"

// locales/fr.toml
items_one   = \"\{\{count}} element\"
items_other = \"\{\{count}} elements\"
greeting    = \"Bonjour, \{\{0}} !\""
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// Pluralization — picks _one or _other key
p \"\{t(\"items\", 1)}\"       // → \"1 item\"
p \"\{t(\"items\", count)}\"   // → \"3 items\" (reactive)

// Positional substitution
p \"\{t(\"greeting\", username)}\"  // → \"Hello, Alice!\""
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Call" }
                    th { "Behaviour" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr { td { code { "t(\"key\")" } } td { "Simple lookup — returns the value or the key if missing" } }
                    tr { td { code { "t(\"key\", n)" } } td { "Number → picks _one (n=1) or _other, replaces \{\{count}}" } }
                    tr { td { code { "t(\"key\", val)" } } td { "Non-number → replaces \{\{0}} with val" } }
                }
            }
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 { "WebAssembly (WASM)" }
        p {
            "Place a Rust crate in "
            code { "wasm/" }
            ". The compiler detects it, runs "
            code { "wasm-pack" }
            ", and injects an async loader — no manual wiring."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// wasm/src/lib.rs
use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;
#[wasm_bindgen]
pub fn compute(n: u32) -> u32 { n * n }

// WebCore component
component WasmDemo {
    state { result: Number = 0 }
    view {
        button on:click=\{result = wasm.compute(result)} { \"Compute\" }
        p \"Result: \{result}\"
    }
}"
        }
        div class="callout" {
            code { "globalThis.wasm" }
            " is populated asynchronously after the module loads. "
            "A full "
            code { "bind()" }
            " call fires on success so any interpolation using "
            code { "wasm.*" }
            " reflects the initial state immediately. The WASM loader is tree-shaken out when no "
            code { "wasm/" }
            " directory is present."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 { "Runtime tree-shaking" }
        p {
            "The compiler emits only the runtime functions actually used by the document. "
            "Unused helpers are never written to the output bundle."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// Minimal bundle — no @for, @if, validation, routing, or WASM
class State {
  #d=new Map(); #l=new Map();
  set(k,v){ this.#d.set(k,v); this.#l.get(k)?.forEach(f=>f(v)) }
  setQ(k,v){ this.#d.set(k,v) }
  get(k){ return this.#d.get(k) }
  on(k,f){ (this.#l.get(k)??this.#l.set(k,[]).get(k)).push(f) }
}
const S = new State();
// bindIf, bindFor, bindAttrs, nav, validateField — absent"
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Function / constant" }
                    th { "Emitted when…" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr { td { code { "bindFor()" } } td { "At least one " code { "@for" } " loop" } }
                    tr { td { code { "bindIf()" } } td { "At least one " code { "@if" } " / " code { "@else" } } }
                    tr { td { code { "bindAttrs()" } } td { "At least one " code { "attr=\{expr}" } " dynamic attribute" } }
                    tr { td { code { "validateField()" } } td { "At least one " code { "validate:*" } " or " code { "@error" } } }
                    tr { td { code { "nav() + popstate" } } td { "Routes declared or " code { "webcore_navigate()" } " used" } }
                    tr { td { code { "DESTROY_HOOKS" } } td { "At least one " code { "on:destroy {}" } " block" } }
                    tr { td { code { "COMPUTED + rebindComputed()" } } td { "At least one " code { "computed {}" } " block" } }
                    tr { td { "WASM loader" } td { code { "wasm/Cargo.toml" } " present at build time" } }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            strong { "How it works: " }
            code { "detect_features()" }
            " in "
            code { "codegen/js/mod.rs" }
            " walks the AST once before code generation and sets boolean flags per feature. Each emitter checks its flag before writing — unused helpers are never serialised to the output file."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "Fine-grained signals ("
            code { "$effect" }
            ") + HMR "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.0.0" }
        }
        p {
            code { "$effect(fn)" }
            " replaces manually subscribing to every state variable. The runtime tracks which variables "
            code { "fn" }
            " reads on its first execution and re-runs it only when those specific variables change."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component Search {
    state { query: String = \"\" results: List = [] }

    // Automatically re-runs whenever query changes
    $effect({
        results = filterItems(S.get('query'))
    })

    view {
        input bind:value=\{query} placeholder=\"Search…\"
        @for r in results { li \"\{r}\" }
    }
}"
        }
        p {
            "HMR: "
            code { "webc serve" }
            " opens a WebSocket connection between the dev server and the browser. On any source change the compiler rebuilds the affected file and sends a reload signal — no configuration needed."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "Security — CSP + SRI + path traversal "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.3.0 – v2.5.0" }
        }
        p { "WebCore ships three independent security layers." }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Feature" }
                    th { "Since" }
                    th { "What it does" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "Path traversal guard" } }
                        td { "v2.0.0" }
                        td { code { "resolve_safe_path()" } " canonicalises every URL served by " code { "webc serve" } "; requests outside " code { "dist/" } " return 403." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "SRI" } }
                        td { "v2.3.0" }
                        td { "In " code { "prod" } " mode, " code { "<script>" } " and " code { "<link>" } " tags receive " code { "integrity=\"sha256-…\"" } " + " code { "crossorigin=\"anonymous\"" } ". Hash computed by the Rust compiler." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "Navigation URL escaping" } }
                        td { "v2.3.0" }
                        td { "Apostrophes and backslashes in " code { "webcore_navigate()" } " calls are escaped — prevents JS injection via crafted route paths." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "Strict CSP — event delegation" } }
                        td { "v2.5.0" }
                        td { "All inline " code { "onclick=" } "/" code { "onsubmit=" } " replaced by " code { "data-webcore-e" } " + delegated listener. Set " code { "csp = true" } " in " code { "webc.toml" } " to also emit the " code { "Content-Security-Policy" } " meta tag." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "ReDoS warning" } }
                        td { "v2.2.0" }
                        td { code { "validate:pattern" } " with nested quantifiers (" code { ")+" } ", " code { ")*" } ") emits " code { "warning[security]" } " at compile time." }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout" {
            strong { "CSP in webc.toml: " }
            pre class="inline-code" {
"[app]
title = \"My App\"
csp   = true      # emits Content-Security-Policy meta"
            }
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "Critical CSS + HTML minification "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.2.0 – v2.4.0" }
        }
        p {
            "In "
            code { "mode = \"prod\"" }
            " the compiler applies several output optimisations automatically."
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Optimisation" }
                    th { "Since" }
                    th { "Effect" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "HTML minification" } }
                        td { "v2.2.0" }
                        td { "Comments and inter-tag whitespace stripped — reduces page size." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "CSS scope elision" } }
                        td { "v2.2.0" }
                        td { "Components without a " code { "style {}" } " block don't emit " code { "data-v" } " — cleaner HTML." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "script defer + preload" } }
                        td { "v2.2.0" }
                        td { code { "<script defer>" } " + " code { "<link rel=\"preload\">" } " in " code { "<head>" } " — JS never blocks HTML parsing." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "Zero-JS elision" } }
                        td { "v2.3.0" }
                        td { "Pages with no state, loops, or events emit no " code { "<script>" } " at all." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "Critical CSS inline" } }
                        td { "v2.4.0" }
                        td { "Each page's CSS (global + used components) is inlined in " code { "<style>" } ". " code { "theme.css" } " loads deferred — zero render-blocking CSS." }
                    }
                    tr {
                        td { strong { "Image fingerprinting" } }
                        td { "v2.4.0" }
                        td { "Every image in " code { "public/" } " receives a FNV-1a content hash (" code { "logo.a3f9c1b2.png" } "). All HTML/CSS references updated — perfect cache busting." }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            strong { "Enable prod mode: " }
            "Set "
            code { "mode = \"prod\"" }
            " in your "
            code { "webc.toml" }
            ". Dev mode keeps full whitespace, no minification, no SRI — faster incremental rebuilds."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "SSG collections "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.4.0" }
        }
        p {
            "Generate one static page per entry in a data file — no server needed for content-driven sites."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"// app.webc — import posts.json, generate one page per entry
import posts from \"data/posts.json\"

app MyBlog {
    routes {
        \"/\":            HomePage
        \"/post/:slug\":  PostPage each posts
    }
}

// PostPage.webc — $route.slug is pre-rendered at build time
page \"post\" {
    h1 \"\{$route.slug}\"
    p \"\{$route.date}\"
}"
        }
        div class="callout" {
            "Output paths are validated with "
            code { "canonicalize()" }
            " — a crafted slug cannot escape "
            code { "dist/" }
            "."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "v2.10.0 – v2.10.1 highlights "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.10.1" }
        }
        p { "Five new DSL features, build optimisations, LSP rename, and three browser-compatibility fixes." }

        h3 { "@defer { } — lazy render block" }
        p {
            "Wrap non-critical content in "
            code { "@defer { }" }
            " to hide it during hydration ("
            code { "display:none" }
            ") and reveal it once "
            code { "DOMContentLoaded" }
            " fires. Eliminates flicker without a separate loading state."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component Hero {
    view {
        h1 \"Welcome\"
        @defer {
            HeavyWidget {}
        }
    }
}"
        }

        h3 { "Shorthand props" }
        p {
            code { "<Component \{count}>" }
            " is sugar for "
            code { "<Component count=\{count}>" }
            " — pass a variable whose name matches the prop. Round-trip preserved by "
            code { "webc fmt" }
            "."
        }

        h3 { "Spread attributes" }
        p {
            code { "<div ...attrs>" }
            " spreads the properties of an expression object as individual DOM attributes at runtime via "
            code { "bindAttrs" }
            "."
        }

        h3 { "LSP textDocument/rename" }
        p {
            "The built-in LSP server now supports "
            code { "textDocument/rename" }
            " — rename a state variable, prop, or identifier across all occurrences in the file with a single editor command."
        }

        h3 { "Content-hash JS filename" }
        p {
            "The compiled runtime is emitted as "
            code { "webcore.<fnv8>.js" }
            " instead of "
            code { "webcore.js?v=hash" }
            ". The hash is in the filename so CDNs cache-bust correctly without query-param tricks."
        }

        h3 { "Browser-compatibility fixes (v2.10.1)" }
        p {
            code { "RegExp.escape()" }
            " (Chrome 127+ only) and "
            code { "Promise.try()" }
            " (Chrome 130+ only) removed from the runtime — replaced with equivalent ES2022 constructs. Also fixed: the prod attribute strip no longer removes the "
            code { "data-webcore-class-bound" }
            " sentinel, which broke class bindings silently after SPA navigation."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "v2.8.0 highlights "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.8.0" }
        }
        p { "Three new features: reactive List mutations, HTTP sugar syntax, and a built-in LSP server." }

        h3 { "Reactive List methods" }
        p {
            "Mutate "
            code { "List" }
            " state variables directly in event handlers — no spread syntax needed."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component TodoList {
    state { todos: List = null }
    view {
        input ref:draft=true placeholder=\"New task\"
        button on:click=\{todos.push(refs.draft.value)} { \"Add\" }
        @for todo, i in todos {
            li {
                \"\{todo}\"
                button on:click=\{todos.remove(i)} { \"×\" }
            }
        }
        button on:click=\{todos.clear()} { \"Clear all\" }
    }
}"
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Method" }
                    th { "Compiled to" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr { td { code { "items.push(val)" } } td { code { "S.set('items',[...S.get('items'),val])" } } }
                    tr { td { code { "items.remove(i)" } } td { code { "S.set('items',S.get('items').filter((_,_i)=>_i!==(i)))" } } }
                    tr { td { code { "items.clear()" } } td { code { "S.set('items',[])" } } }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            "Works on store variables too: "
            code { "$store.cart.push(item)" }
            " compiles to "
            code { "STORE.set('cart',[...STORE.get('cart'),item])" }
            "."
        }

        h3 { "@loading / @catch" }
        p {
            "Shorthand for "
            code { "@if loading" }
            " and "
            code { "@if error" }
            " inside HTTP components."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component Posts {
    state { posts: List = null }
    http { get: \"/api/posts\"  into: posts }
    view {
        @loading {
            p \"Loading…\"
        }
        @catch {
            p class=\"error\" \"Error: \{error}\"
        }
        @for post in posts {
            article { h2 \"\{post.title}\" }
        }
    }
}"
        }
        div class="callout" {
            code { "@loading" }
            " and "
            code { "@catch" }
            " compile directly to "
            code { "Element::If" }
            " nodes — no runtime changes, zero overhead."
        }

        h3 { "Built-in LSP server" }
        p {
            "Run "
            code { "webc lsp" }
            " to start a Language Server Protocol 3.17 server on stdin/stdout. "
            "Wire it to any LSP-capable editor for hover docs, completions, and jump-to-definition."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"# VS Code settings.json (example)
{
  \"languageServerExample.serverOptions\": {
    \"command\": \"webc\",
    \"args\": [\"lsp\"]
  }
}"
        }
        div class="table-wrap" {
            table {
                thead { tr {
                    th { "Capability" }
                    th { "Description" }
                } }
                tbody {
                    tr { td { code { "textDocument/hover" } } td { "Docs for the symbol under the cursor" } }
                    tr { td { code { "textDocument/completion" } } td { "Keywords, blocks, and directives" } }
                    tr { td { code { "textDocument/definition" } } td { "Jump to component or variable definition" } }
                    tr { td { "Sync" } td { code { "didOpen" } " / " code { "didChange" } " / " code { "didClose" } } }
                }
            }
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            strong { "Zero extra dependencies: " }
            "The LSP server is implemented in pure Rust using only "
            code { "serde_json" }
            " (already a compiler dependency). No separate language server binary to install."
        }
    }

    section class="doc-section" {
        h2 {
            "v2.6.0 highlights "
            span class="version-tag" { "v2.6.0" }
        }
        p { "Three new syntax features and one new CLI command." }

        h3 { "Fragment shorthand" }
        p {
            code { "<>...</>" }
            " groups elements without a wrapper tag. Renders inline — no intermediate "
            code { "<div>" }
            " in the output."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component TwoItems {
    view {
        <>
            p \"First\"
            p \"Second\"
        </>
    }
}
// Output: <p>First</p><p>Second</p>"
        }

        h3 { "Event modifiers" }
        p {
            "Control listener behaviour with "
            code { "|stop" }
            ", "
            code { "|prevent" }
            ", "
            code { "|once" }
            ", "
            code { "|self" }
            " — no boilerplate JS."
        }
        pre class="code-block" {
"form on:submit|prevent=\{handleSubmit} { ... }
button on:click|stop=\{count += 1} { \"+\" }
button on:click|once=\{welcomed = true} { \"Welcome\" }
div on:click|self=\{toggle} { span { \"child\" } }"
        }

        h3 { "Default prop values" }
        pre class="code-block" {
"component Badge {
    props { label: String = \"N/A\"  color: String = \"gray\" }
    view { span class=\{color} \"\{label}\" }
}
Badge {}              // uses defaults
Badge label=\"OK\" {}  // color defaults to gray"
        }

        h3 { "webc watch" }
        p {
            code { "webc watch" }
            " rebuilds on every source file change without starting a dev server — useful for CI pipelines and headless build workflows."
        }
        div class="callout-tip" {
            "Run "
            code { "webc serve" }
            " for interactive development with HMR. Use "
            code { "webc watch" }
            " when you only need the output files."
        }
    }
}
